The paper discusses a new sorting algorithm and provides theoretical analysis of its performance, making it likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AL (Computational Complexity and Algorithms) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of other sorting algorithms like Heapsort, Insertionsort, and Mergesort, which falls under the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The paper also provides transfer theorems and examines the possibility of sorting base cases with some other algorithm, which falls under the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions challenging established library implementations, which falls under the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
